reviewText: The Jersey Shore is rocked by a prehistoric species of sharks after an illegal drilling operation awakens them from an underwater cave, leaving it is up to a group of greased-up party-goers to save the day! Yes, it is as bad as it sounds, and no, Roger Corman did not produce it. JERSEY SHORE SHARK ATTACK combines the two worst things television has to offer in to an hour-and-a-half of sheer stupidity. Luckily, characters Donnie, Nooki, TC "The Complication," and others provide a few cheap laughs along the way as they spoof their MTV counterparts. The editing and sound design playfully poke fun at the television series as well, although no amount of scripted humor can ever compare to the natural idiocy of Jersey Shore. JERSEY SHORE SHARK ATTACK proudly boasts some of the worst computer-generated sharks that mankind has ever known. One can only hope that the designers were in on the joke, and intended for the sharks to look this terrible. At the very least, visitors to the Jersey Shore are filled with explosive geysers of blood, and make for many tasty snacks. As awful as the film may be, it has the same captivating effect as the MTV show. It is impossible to look away for fear of what you might miss. Coming soon to dollar bins everywhere alongside SPRING BREAK SHARK ATTACK, MEGA PIRANHA, and DINOSHARK.-Carl ManesI Like Horror Movies

reviewText: Let me start off by saying, I love B-Movie Creature Features, hell I even have a soft side for Piranha 3DD and the Lake Placid Sequels.... But when a movie has everything wrong with it... I get pissed.  To tell you in all honesty, I hated the characters.... I realize that this movie is not meant to be taken seriously and I can accept that but when a movie has such annoying characters.... I am just glad I don't watch Jersey Shore that's all I have to say about that. As for the film itself, yeah.... It was pretty much epically cheesy.Plot: Jersey Shore, a wild place for spring breakers and locals to enjoy.... But when an oil rig disturbs a sleeping ground (or something) for albino sharks with glowing red eyes, the bloodbath will begin and it'll be up to the mocks of the jersey shore characters to save the day!Review: In my opinion I thought that if they had done a movie where the first half or at least first quarter could've taken place in 1916 with the real jersey shore shark attacks it would've been a bit better even if it were to be a bit long, but I guess the makers of this movie (which included Fred Olen Ray, Director of Super Shark, Dire Wolf, and hell even Silent Venom) saw 12 Days of Terror and thought well, guess it is time to move onto the jersey Shore Cast.... And don't get me wrong, I like Fred Olen Rays Movies, most of the time but Jersey Shore Shark Attack was so over the top.... I mean yeah it was stupid with annoying characters but there are two ways you can make a movie's plot when its title is Jersey Shore Shark Attack, you can make it serious like 12 Days of Terror, or you can make basically a fun mockery of other shark flicks and throw in the Jersey Shores Cast. The CGI sharks were incredibly laughable and I usually try to look out for the best in the bad CGI department and I only noticed like one decent CG shot and that was with a shark ramming its frigging head into a pear.... These are without a doubt the worst CG sharks I've ever seen and trust me when I say, I have seen them all. The gore was there but farfetched and the soundtrack consisted of hip-hop and rap and I just couldn't stand it.... Jersey Shore Shark Attack was a total cheese fest and I think the movie would've been much better without the mock cast of the members of Jersey Shore. I remember when this movie came out in June and it was the first of three other movies to come on Syfy Channel that month and it was the first, but the clear better one was Piranhaconda which had immensely better CGI and characters and gore and action, Arachnoquake and Bigfoot followed and they were way better than this movie. I don't want to sound like I'm ranting because this film isn't 100% bad; it's just only 30% of it is good.Acting: Please Don't Make Me!Gore: To be honest this is the only shark movie I've ever scene where someone's guts gets ripped out. That being said, we also get nasty yet over-the-top severed fingers, a severed arm, lots of red water, and uh, oh yeah... lots and lots of blood spraying.... It had such over the top gore but it was gory so I shall give it credit for that.Bottom Line: This is one of the worst shark movies I've ever seen on Syfy but then again it was better than Shark Zone or the Shark Attack Trilogy.... It wasn't the worst shark movie ever but it was definitely the worst shark movie of the year in my opinion.  It was a little under decent and truly a heavily shaken mixed bag for me. Ending on a good note I dug the cheesy feel the movie had and the editing was fun to watch.Rated R for Some Bloody Creature ViolenceIs it worth the Buy on a scale of 1-10: 2For the Movie itself on a scale of 1-5: 2
summary: It wasn't bad, but it wasn't that great either.

reviewText: In "Jersey Shore Shark Attack" Fred Olen Ray produces another masterwork, this time marrying parodies of every shark movie in history and "Jersey Shore." Featuring nothing but stereotypes with cast names like "The Complication," "Nooki," and "Paulie Balzac," special cameos from the likes of Tony Sirico and Joey Fatone (who gives a hilariously and mercifully brief concert,) and some of the worst effects in history (even for a SyFy movie,) this film requires you to approach it from the right viewpoint to enjoy it at all. If you want to see a traditionally "good" movie the title alone should be all you need to know. If you want to see some hokey acting superimposed on a ridiculous plot and can bear the cast slathering on the hair oil and sporting the Bumpit hair to the max, this is a film you will likely revel in.The biggest detractor from the movie is how slow it gets when the ancillary subplots rear their heads: tales of the 1916 boardwalk shark attack (told by "Sopranos" tough guy Tony Sirico, who even gets to say "Bada bing!" while really lame sound effects complete the scene,) the yacht club types vs. the Jersey Shore types, the police department tie-in, the new construction nonsense all help bring the movie to a crawl when the director could be spending a lot more time on the red-eyed albino sharks marauding off New Jersey on July fourth. (Of course that would increase the effects budget which is evidently paltry to start with.) Pacing really is the Achilles heel here, as when the guys are involved with the sharks it's modestly amusing low-budget B-movie mayhem.At any rate, the film is nothing if not predictable, and people who enjoy the ludicrousness of the SyFy original movies will likely enjoy this one. It's terribly made, although the cast does a generally good job with their very over-the-top roles, and there are some amusing cameos (here I must reemphasize the point that the Joey Fatone appearance is the best part of the film.) The film has everything you'd expect from this genre: terrible dialogue, senseless plotpoints, no sense of style, gratuitous use of fireworks, wretched music and associated dancing, and hilariously bad effects. If you are searching for these qualities in a movie let me recommend "Jersey Shore Shark Attack." If you are not seeking these attributes in a motion picture, I would definitely abstain.
summary: "You Really Think You're Going To Attract Sharks With Protein Bars?"

reviewText: I know people have given this film some of the worst reviews and feel it's a terrible film, but personally after seeing the film I thought it was quite funny.  First off I never watch movies featuring any member of a boy band acting and yes this does include Justin Timberlake.  To this date I have never seen a movie with Justin Timberlake in it and I just cannot bring myself to enjoy Justin Timberlake as an actor because of what boy bands did to the music scene in the late 1990's.  Boy bands/teanie boppers who don't write their own songs or take the time to find anyone who knows what their doing to write their songs for them IE Justin Bieber and Britney Spears kind killed the music industry in the late 1990's.  But for this film, I will make an exception since Joey Futone of N'Sync or should I say N'Suck plays himself so he can be mocked in the film and killed by a shark jumping out of the water and biting his head off in his mockery.Now before I get to the plot of this film, I would like to take time to say what I appreciate it making fun of in posers like Joey Futone who ruined the music industry in the 1990's and stupid reality shows like Jersey Shore that ruined MTV in the 1990's (OK, The Real World is what started ruining MTV in the 1990's, but Jersey Shore is still that type of show, even though it didn't air till this past decade).  Basically this show is about some guitos (Jersey Shore mockery) (TC, Donnie (a mockery of Pauly on Jersey shore), Blazac, Nookie, J-Moni (mockeries of Snooki and Jwoww on Jersey shore), and BJ) who see a few preppy rich kids (Bradford and Spencer) chase one of their friends (JP) who is a DJ and a strong swimmer into the ocean, because of a riot the preppy kids started at a bar.  After JP is chased into the ocean, he is pronounced dead due to drowning by the local Jersey police on the board walk.  But TC tells the rest of his guito friends that JP was killed by a shark after finding his hat with bite marks on it.  Then the guitos investigate a rocky shore and find a species of Albino Bull Shark responsible for killing their friend.  Then the guitos try to warn everyone on the boardwalk about the sharks and are laughed at by everyone until Joey Futone dies while singing in a concert on the board walk.  Then the Jersey police find out that the sharks had been attracted by the movements of illegal oil drilling in the ocean.  I can't tell you the rest of the movie, because it would Spoil too much.Now as mentioned earlier this movie is quite funny.  Must see funny portions of this movie include, the sharks killing people, the sharks poping up over the railing of boats. Joey Futone's death (funniest scene of the movie), that sharks biting down a pear, sharks sinking a yacht, and just the way Joey Futone and Jersey shore are mocked in the movie.  Then there's that scene when Nookie hits a shark poping over the side of a yacht with an oar.  But don't be fooled by these scenes in reality no shark including the bull has ever killed anyone while they are on land nor have they ever sank a yacht or damaged any portion of a pier or boardwalk, even though some species of shark including the bull have been known to attack boats.  And even though there's about a 99% chance you won't get attacked by a bull shark in the wild, I would strongly advise not swimming with them since it is extremely rare anyone gets away from being attacked by a bull shark in the wild.  But if you do see a shark of any type in the wild, what I would strongly advise doing is quickly and calmly (more calmly then quickly) swimming to shore and running to the life guard to tell them there is a shark in the water.  Remember, people only make sharks viscous man eaters in movies to make money, no species of shark is that way in reality even though there are species of shark that do eat people.And on my final note, I would like to say that because Joey Futone dies in this movie it gets 5 stars.
summary: I don't know why everyone hates this film

reviewerName: The Movie Guy "Movies from A to Z"
reviewText: The Jersey Shore is under attack by CG generated red-eyed albino "Moby Dick" sharks. This is a campy cleavage filled take off of "Jersey Shore" and shark attack movies. The production utilizes Troma style blood squirts and occasional body parts. The dialouge ranges from clever to sad and includes many bad shark attack lines such as: "You're not half the man I am."Spoofs include hunting sharks with Roman candles and M-80s. Typical shark movie criticisms include deep water sharks in shallow water and people seen standing in water in one scene are shown treading water from underneath. Cameo appearance by Joey Fatone, who I discovered is his real name and not a gag name (Fat one) although one can't help but think that in this film.Enjoyable Snooki spoof. I don't watch "Jersey Shore" and don't know of anyone who admits to it, but everyone knows Snooki. I am sure "Jersey Shore" fans will have more to howl about in this film.PARENTAL GUIDE: No f-bombs, sex, or nudity. Implied sex with couple in bed on morning after. Lame wet t-shirt contest with contestants wearing bikini tops under shirts...I mean what's the point? 4 stars for those who like bad campy films.
